{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1672,"text":"I have spent the past 38 years\ntrying to be invisible."},{"time":7830,"text":"I'm a copy editor."},{"time":9807,"text":"I work at The New Yorker,"},{"time":11531,"text":"and copyediting for The New Yorker\nis like playing shortstop"},{"time":15729,"text":"for a Major League Baseball team:"},{"time":17967,"text":"every little movement\ngets picked over by the critics --"},{"time":21404,"text":"God forbid you should commit an error."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25086,"text":"Just to clarify: copy editors don't choose\nwhat goes into the magazine."},{"time":29530,"text":"We work at the level of the sentence,"},{"time":31932,"text":"maybe the paragraph,"},{"time":33644,"text":"the words, the punctuation."},{"time":36175,"text":"Our business is in the details."},{"time":38904,"text":"We put the diaeresis, the double dot,\nover the \"i\" in \"naïve.\""},{"time":44591,"text":"We impose house style."},{"time":46542,"text":"Every publication has a house style."},{"time":49252,"text":"The New Yorker's\nis particularly distinctive."},{"time":52503,"text":"We sometimes get teased for our style."},{"time":55307,"text":"Imagine -- we still spell\n\"teen-ager\" with a hyphen,"},{"time":59671,"text":"as if that word had just been coined."},{"time":62919,"text":"But you see that hyphen in \"teen-age\""},{"time":66543,"text":"and that diaeresis over \"coöperate,\""},{"time":69159,"text":"and you know you're reading\nThe New Yorker."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71850,"text":"Copyediting at The New Yorker\nis a mechanical process."},{"time":75372,"text":"There is a related role called\nquery proofreading,"},{"time":78595,"text":"or page-OK'ing."},{"time":80959,"text":"Whereas copyediting is mechanical,"},{"time":83753,"text":"query proofreading is interpretive."},{"time":86696,"text":"We make suggestions to the author\nthrough the editor"},{"time":90092,"text":"to improve the emphasis of a sentence"},{"time":92737,"text":"or point out unintentional repetitions"},{"time":95395,"text":"and supply compelling alternatives."},{"time":100502,"text":"Our purpose is to make\nthe author look good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103504,"text":"Note that we give our proofs\nnot directly to the author,"},{"time":106857,"text":"but to the editor."},{"time":108400,"text":"This often creates\na good cop/bad cop dynamic"},{"time":112541,"text":"in which the copy editor -- I'll use that\nas an umbrella term --"},{"time":116089,"text":"is invariably the bad cop."},{"time":120008,"text":"If we do our job well, we're invisible,"},{"time":122469,"text":"but as soon as we make a mistake,"},{"time":124565,"text":"we copy editors become glaringly visible."},{"time":129426,"text":"Here is the most recent mistake\nthat was laid at my door."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133931,"text":"[Last Tuesday, Sarah Palin,\nthe pre-Trump embodiment"},{"time":137479,"text":"of populist no-nothingism\nin the Republican Party,"},{"time":140649,"text":"endorsed Trump.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":142935,"text":"\"Where were The New Yorker's fabled\ncopy editors?\" a reader wrote."},{"time":147167,"text":"\"Didn't the writer mean\n'know-nothingism'?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":150789,"text":"Ouch."},{"time":152090,"text":"There's no excuse for this mistake."},{"time":154786,"text":"But I like it: \"no-nothingism.\""},{"time":157899,"text":"It might be American\nvernacular for \"nihilism.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":161881,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165112,"text":"Here, another reader quotes\na passage from the magazine:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":168160,"text":"[Ruby was seventy-six, but she retained\nher authoritative bearing;"},{"time":172221,"text":"only her unsteady gait belied her age.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":176770,"text":"He added:"},{"time":177945,"text":"\"Surely, someone at The New Yorker\nknows the meaning of 'belied,'"},{"time":181052,"text":"and that it is the opposite\nof how it is used in this sentence."},{"time":184284,"text":"Come on! Get it together.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":186648,"text":"Belie: to give a false impression."},{"time":190180,"text":"It should have been \"betrayed.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":193426,"text":"E.B. White once wrote\nof commas in The New Yorker:"},{"time":196325,"text":"\"They fall with the precision\nof knives outlining a body.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":201213,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":202939,"text":"And it's true -- we get a lot\nof complaints about commas."},{"time":206124,"text":"\"Are there really two commas\nin 'Martin Luther King, Jr., Boulevard'?\""},{"time":210746,"text":"There may not be on the sign, but yes,\nthat is New Yorker style for \"Jr.\""},{"time":216192,"text":"One wag wrote:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":218181,"text":"[\"Please, could you expel,\nor, at least, restrain,"},{"time":221647,"text":"the comma-maniac,\non your editorial staff?\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":224695,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":226071,"text":"Ah, well."},{"time":227246,"text":"In this case, those commas\nare well-placed,"},{"time":229514,"text":"except that there should not be one"},{"time":231409,"text":"between \"maniac\" and \"on.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":233435,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":234694,"text":"Also, if we must have commas\naround \"at least,\""},{"time":238466,"text":"we might change it up\nby using dashes around that phrase:"},{"time":242530,"text":"\"... -- or, at least, restrain --\""},{"time":246392,"text":"Perfect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247586,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":249188,"text":"Then there's this:"},{"time":250547,"text":"\"Love you, love your magazine,"},{"time":252009,"text":"but can you please stop writing\nmassive numbers as text?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":257230,"text":"[two and a half million ...]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":258808,"text":"No."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259991,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":262053,"text":"One last cri de coeur\nfrom a spelling stickler:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":265179,"text":"[\"Those long stringy things\nare vocal cords, not chords.\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":270347,"text":"The outraged reader added,"},{"time":272520,"text":"\"I'm sure I'm not the first to write"},{"time":274377,"text":"regarding this egregious\nproofreading error,"},{"time":277622,"text":"but I'm equally sure I won't be the last."},{"time":280052,"text":"Fie!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":281296,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":283541,"text":"I used to like getting mail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287222,"text":"There is a pact\nbetween writers and editors."},{"time":289842,"text":"The editor never sells out the writer,"},{"time":292245,"text":"never goes public about bad jokes\nthat had to be cut"},{"time":295821,"text":"or stories that went on too long."},{"time":298295,"text":"A great editor saves a writer\nfrom her excesses."},{"time":303558,"text":"Copy editors, too, have a code;"},{"time":305610,"text":"we don't advertise our oversights."},{"time":308593,"text":"I feel disloyal divulging them here,"},{"time":311317,"text":"so let's have look at what we do right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315570,"text":"Somehow, I've gotten\na reputation for sternness."},{"time":319133,"text":"But I work with writers who know\nhow to have their way with me."},{"time":323741,"text":"I've known Ian Frazier, or \"Sandy,\"\nsince the early 80s."},{"time":327913,"text":"And he's one of my favorites,"},{"time":329566,"text":"even though he sometimes writes a sentence"},{"time":332035,"text":"that gives a copy editor pause."},{"time":334846,"text":"Here is one from a story\nabout Staten Island"},{"time":337404,"text":"after Hurricane Sandy:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":340092,"text":"[A dock that had been broken\nin the middle and lost its other half"},{"time":344125,"text":"sloped down toward the water,"},{"time":346533,"text":"its support pipes and wires\nleaning forward"},{"time":350237,"text":"like when you open a box\nof linguine and it slides out.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":354072,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":355350,"text":"This would never have got past\nthe grammarian in the days of yore."},{"time":360504,"text":"But what could I do?"},{"time":361767,"text":"Technically, the \"like\" should be an \"as,\""},{"time":364395,"text":"but it sounds ridiculous,"},{"time":365863,"text":"as if the author were about to embark\non an extended Homeric simile --"},{"time":370211,"text":"\"as when you open a box of linguine.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":373395,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":374728,"text":"I decided that the hurricane\nconferred poetic justice on Sandy"},{"time":379528,"text":"and let the sentence stand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381203,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":382314,"text":"Generally, if I think something is wrong,"},{"time":384346,"text":"I query it three times."},{"time":385862,"text":"I told Sandy that not long ago\nin a moment of indiscretion and he said,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":389741,"text":"\"Only three?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":391276,"text":"So, he has learned to hold out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393044,"text":"Recently, he wrote a story\nfor \"Talk of the Town,\""},{"time":395467,"text":"that's the section\nat the front of the magazine"},{"time":397712,"text":"with short pieces on subjects\nranging from Ricky Jay's exhibit"},{"time":400814,"text":"at the Metropolitan Museum"},{"time":402383,"text":"to the introduction\nof doggie bags in France."},{"time":405578,"text":"Sandy's story was about\nthe return to the Bronx"},{"time":408020,"text":"of Supreme Court Justice Sonia Sotomayor."},{"time":410711,"text":"There were three things\nin it that I had to challenge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413284,"text":"First, a grammar query."},{"time":414872,"text":"The justice was wearing black\nand Sandy wrote,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":417491,"text":"[Her face and hands stood out\nlike in an old, mostly dark painting.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":423043,"text":"Now, unlike with the hurricane,"},{"time":425017,"text":"with this \"like,\" the author\ndidn't have the excuse"},{"time":427509,"text":"of describing hurricane damage."},{"time":429340,"text":"\"Like\" in this sense is a preposition,\nand a preposition takes an object,"},{"time":433660,"text":"which is a noun."},{"time":434877,"text":"This \"like\" had to be an \"as.\""},{"time":437433,"text":"\"As in an old, mostly dark painting.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":440615,"text":"Second, a spelling issue."},{"time":442289,"text":"The author was quoting someone\nwho was assisting the justice:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":445986,"text":"[\"It will be just a minute."},{"time":447432,"text":"We are getting the justice mic'ed,\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":451434,"text":"Mic'ed?"},{"time":452982,"text":"The music industry spells it \"mic\""},{"time":455003,"text":"because that's how it's spelled\non the equipment."},{"time":457385,"text":"I'd never seen it used\nas a verb with this spelling,"},{"time":459836,"text":"and I was distraught\nto think that \"mic'ed\""},{"time":462390,"text":"would get into the magazine on my watch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464699,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":465734,"text":"New Yorker style for \"microphone\"\nin its abbreviated form is \"mike.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":470519,"text":"Finally, there was a sticky\ngrammar and usage issue"},{"time":473170,"text":"in which the pronoun has to have\nthe same grammatical number"},{"time":476908,"text":"as its antecedent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479292,"text":"[everyone in the vicinity\nheld their breath]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":483491,"text":"\"Their\" is plural and \"everyone,\"\nits antecedent, is singular."},{"time":487710,"text":"You would never say,\n\"Everyone were there.\""},{"time":490672,"text":"Everyone was there. Everyone is here."},{"time":494537,"text":"But people say things like,\n\"Everyone held their breath\" all the time."},{"time":498175,"text":"To give it legitimacy,"},{"time":499418,"text":"copy editors call it\n\"the singular 'their,'\""},{"time":502865,"text":"as if calling it singular\nmakes it no longer plural."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505954,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":507372,"text":"It is my job when I see it in print\nto do my best to eliminate it."},{"time":513370,"text":"I couldn't make it,\n\"Everyone held her breath,\""},{"time":515872,"text":"or \"Everyone held his breath,\""},{"time":517588,"text":"or \"Everyone held his or her breath.\""},{"time":520174,"text":"Whatever I suggested had to blend in."},{"time":523018,"text":"I asked, through the editor,"},{"time":524398,"text":"if the author would consider changing it"},{"time":526470,"text":"to \"All in the vicinity\nheld their breath,\""},{"time":529065,"text":"because \"all\" is plural."},{"time":530931,"text":"Nope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532112,"text":"I tried again: \"All those present\nheld their breath?\""},{"time":535366,"text":"I thought this sounded vaguely judicial."},{"time":537611,"text":"But the editor pointed out"},{"time":538882,"text":"that we could not have \"present\"\nand \"presence\""},{"time":541311,"text":"in the same sentence."},{"time":543108,"text":"When the final proof came back,"},{"time":544711,"text":"the author had accepted \"as\" for \"like,\""},{"time":547311,"text":"and \"miked\" for \"mic'ed.\""},{"time":549270,"text":"But on \"Everyone held their breath,\"\nhe stood his ground."},{"time":553490,"text":"Two out of three isn't bad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556010,"text":"In the same issue,"},{"time":557277,"text":"in that piece on doggie bags in France,"},{"time":559823,"text":"there was the gratuitous use\nof the f-word by a Frenchman."},{"time":564260,"text":"I wonder, when the mail comes in,"},{"time":566888,"text":"which will have offended the readers more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569770,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":571467,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572642,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}